# Design System Architecture

- This repository is `@handled-ai/design-system`, a shared component library used by multiple apps.
- Primary distribution channel is npm (`@handled-ai/design-system`) built with `npm run build:lib` (tsup).
- The shadcn registry/Vercel site is secondary and used for showcase/discovery, not production installation.
- Component source files live in `registry/new-york/ui/*.tsx`.
- The npm package entry point is root `index.ts`.
- Documentation lives in:
  - `docs/COMPONENTS.md` (table of contents)
  - `docs/components/{name}.md` (per-component docs)
- Publishing is manual: bump version in `package.json` then run `npm publish`.
- Key scripts: `build:lib`, `registry:build`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `dev`.
- Theming uses semantic CSS variable tokens; consuming apps own token values.

# Component Conventions

- Use functional components.
- Use `cn` from `@/lib/utils` for class merging.
- Accept and forward `className`.
- Use `data-slot` attributes where appropriate for composability/testability.
